If you check the tab **&quot;Network&quot;** from your browser (you can open it by pressing F12), when you make a change in one of the select fields, they send a request to their backend API that is responsable to get the data and send to the frontend.

[![enter image description here][1]][1]

This approach is made using **ajax** which doesn&#39;t require your client to reload his page to make a request your backend. I suggest you take a read [here][2] to clarify how ajax works and how ajax requests works.

Since you&#39;re using **jQuery** already, you can use it to make your ajax request, like bellow:

    $.ajax({
        method: &quot;GET&quot;, // Request method
        url: &quot;retrieve_data.php&quot;, // Path to the file responsable to receive your request and get the data to return to the frontend
        data: {
            data: &quot;my data&quot; // Data to be to your backend
        }
    })

What you basically need to do is, after changing a value in one of the selects, send the new value to your backend (using ajax) get the results related to the requested value and send back to the frontend, so your frontend be responsable to display the updated data.

